  <datafield tag="545" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Mathematics professor at the University of Michigan. Lewis joined the faculty in 1961 and served as chairman of the department, 1984-1994. Active in the American Mathematical Society, Lewis served on the Committee on Publications and the Task Force on Employment. Lewis also worked closely with the National Science Foundation, serving as director of the NSF division of mathematical sciences.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Documentation includes correspondence, departmental material, professional studies and reports on mathematic instruction, careers, and women and minorities in math. Also includes a photograph of Lewis at the ground breaking of the addition to West Hall (including Patricia Gurin and Homer Neal).</subfield>
  </datafield>
